    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 2,
        "summary": "The Lord gives wisdom, knowledge, and understanding\u2014Walk in the way of good men.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "My son, if thou wilt receive my words, and hide my commandments with thee;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0treasure. Prov. 4:21.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "So that thou incline thine ear unto wisdom, and apply thine heart to understanding;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 16:10; 3\u00a0Ne. 19:33.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Yea, if thou criest after knowledge, and liftest up thy voice for understanding;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If thou seekest her as silver, and searchest for her as for hid treasures;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shalt thou understand the fear of the Lord, and find the knowledge of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 36:7.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Knowledge.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the Lord giveth wisdom: out of his mouth cometh knowledge and understanding.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Wisdom of; Wisdom.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Understanding.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He layeth up sound wisdom for the righteous: he is a buckler to them that walk uprightly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 91:4.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He keepeth the paths of judgment, and preserveth the way of his saints.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then shalt thou understand righteousness, and judgment, and equity; yea, every good path.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 28:30.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When wisdom entereth into thine heart, and knowledge is pleasant unto thy soul;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Discretion shall preserve thee, understanding shall keep thee:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rashness.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To deliver thee from the way of the evil man, from the man that speaketh froward things;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Who leave the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking in Darkness.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who rejoice to do evil, and delight in the frowardness of the wicked;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0perverseness.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whose ways are crooked, and they froward in their paths:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To deliver thee from the strange woman, even from the stranger which flattereth with her words;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0alien woman; unchaste women were often so called. Prov. 5:3 (3, 20). TG\u00a0Adulterer.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Which forsaketh the guide of her youth, and forgetteth the covenant of her God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For her house inclineth unto death, and her paths unto the dead.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "None that go unto her return again, neither take they hold of the paths of life.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 7:26.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "That thou mayest walk in the way of good men, and keep the paths of the righteous.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For the upright shall dwell in the land, and the perfect shall remain in it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:30.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the wicked shall be cut off from the earth, and the transgressors shall be rooted out of it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 52:5.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}